dcterms:creator: B. Ylmaz
C. Toker
dcterms:description: The Turkish National Permanent GPS Network (TNPGN) Active dataset is used for generating Total Electron Content (TEC) maps, providing actual measurements for performance evaluation of the proposed compressive sensing technique.
dcterms:title: Turkish National Permanent GPS Network (TNPGN) Active

dcterms:creator: F. Arkan
C. B. Erol
O. Arkan
dcterms:description: IONOLAB-TEC is a signal processing technique used to estimate Vertical Total Electron Content (VTEC) from GPS data, providing a method for calculating TEC values in the local zenith direction.
dcterms:title: IONOLAB-TEC

dcterms:creator: U. Sezen
F. Arkan
O. Arkan
O. Uurlu
A. Sadeghimorad
dcterms:description: This version of IONOLAB-TEC focuses on online, automatic, near-real-time estimation of GPS-based Total Electron Content (TEC), enhancing the temporal resolution of TEC data.
dcterms:title: IONOLAB-TEC (for a different context)

dcterms:description: Global Ionospheric Maps produced by CODE provide a comprehensive view of the ionosphere, useful for various applications in ionospheric research.
dcterms:title: Global Ionospheric Maps

dcterms:description: NASA-JPL (IARS) provides ionospheric and atmospheric remote sensing data, which can be utilized for ionospheric studies and TEC mapping.
dcterms:title: NASA-JPL (IARS)

dcterms:description: DLR (IMPC) focuses on ionosphere monitoring and prediction, providing valuable data for ionospheric research and TEC estimation.
dcterms:title: DLR (IMPC)

dcterms:description: SWS provides space weather data and forecasts, which are essential for understanding ionospheric conditions and their impact on communication systems.
dcterms:title: SWS

dcterms:description: The Australian Government Bureau of Meteorology provides space weather services, contributing to the monitoring and understanding of ionospheric phenomena.
dcterms:title: Australian Government Bureau of Meteorology, Space Weather Services
